content:
Set Up Entitlement and Asset Lookup Filters on Cases

Set up lookup filters on entitlement-related case fields to restrict the entitlements that users can select on a case.

Required Editions and User Permissions:
Available in: Salesforce Classic, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with the Service Cloud
User Permission Needed: Manage Entitlements

To set up entitlement-related lookups on cases:

From Setup, enter Entitlement Settings in the Quick Find box, then select Entitlement Settings.
Choose the item(s) you'd like returned in the lookup fields.

Lookup Field on Cases:
Asset - Same account on the case
Assets registered to the account on the case.
Same contact on the case
Assets registered to the contact on the case.
Entitlements on the case's account
Assets associated with entitlements that belong to the case’s account.
Entitlements on the case's contact
Assets associated with entitlements related to the case’s contact.

Entitlement - Active status
Entitlements with an Active Status.
Same account on the case
Entitlements associated with the account on the case.
Same asset on the case
Entitlements associated with the asset on the case.
Same contact on the case
Entitlements associated with the contact on the case.

Click Save.
title: Setting Up Entitlement Lookup Filters on Cases in Service Cloud
